<TITLE> Physio Lifson due in Dhaka Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 19 (bdnews24.com)  South African physio Darryn Lifson will arrive Tuesday morning to ink a tw0-year deal with Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) as the national cricket team's physiotherapist. Lifson will take over from Australian physio Paul Close. The 28 year-old physio earlier worked for the Pakistan national team, the Pakistan national cricket academy and sports science institute of South Africa, said a press release Monday. Lifson was also the chief physiotherapist for Ajax Cape Town Football Team. 
